    <text>
        <body>
            <listEvent>
                <event>
                    <head xml:lang="en">
                        Identify concepts in the dataset
                    </head>
                    <desc xml:lang="en" corresp="definition">
                        Formalize the data structure : 1/ Data dictionary: for consistency, make explicit the vocabulary used in the data set. 2/ Without reference to CIDOC, identify the high-level concepts that structure the dataset. Think about the relevance of the data to be stored (not necessarily useful to model everything) and make a selection. In order to achieve interoperability, it is not useful to map concepts that are specific to a dataset but to focus on concepts that are shared with other datasets in the discipline. The specificities of a dataset remain accessible and searchable directly in the online corpus of this dataset. 3/ Formalize a diagram linking the concepts together by specifying the relationships. 4/ Identify any metadata intrinsic to the dataset: for a database of an archaeological excavation, the information of the person responsible for the excavation, the name of the site itself, is not necessarily stored in the dataset itself.
                    </desc>
                    <desc corresp="terms">
                        <term key="Modeling" corresp="activity"/>
                    </desc>
